  "local_port": 50874,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are all time best movies to watch?",
  "response": "Creating a list of the \"best\" movies of all time can be subjective, as it often depends on personal preferences, genres, and cultural impact. However, based on critical acclaim, audience reception, and lasting influence, here is a diverse list of some of the all-time best movies across various genres and eras:\n\n### **Classics**\n\n1. **\"Casablanca\" (1942)**\n   - *Directed by Michael Curtiz*\n   - A timeless romance set against the backdrop of World War II, featuring memorable performances by Humphrey Bogart and Ingrid Bergman.\n\n2. **\"Citizen Kane\" (1941)**\n   - *Directed by Orson Welles*\n   - Often cited as one of the greatest films ever made, it explores the life of a publishing tycoon through innovative storytelling techniques.\n\n3. **\"Gone with the Wind\" (1939)**\n   - *Directed by Victor Fleming*\n   - An epic historical romance set during the American Civil War, known for its grand scale and iconic performances.\n\n### **Drama**\n\n4. **\"The Shawshank Redemption\" (1994)**\n   - *Directed by Frank Darabont*\n   - A powerful story of hope and friendship set within a prison, consistently ranking high on audience favorite lists.\n\n5. **\"Forrest Gump\" (1994)**\n   - *Directed by Robert Zemeckis*\n   - Follows the life of a simple man who unwittingly influences several historical events, blending drama and heartwarming moments.\n\n6. **\"Schindler's List\" (1993)**\n   - *Directed by Steven Spielberg*\n   - A harrowing depiction of the Holocaust, telling the true story of Oskar Schindler's efforts to save Jews from the Nazis.\n\n### **Action & Adventure**\n\n7. **\"The Dark Knight\" (2008)**\n   - *Directed by Christopher Nolan*\n   - A superhero film praised for its complex characters, especially Heath Ledger's iconic portrayal of the Joker.\n\n8. **\"Indiana Jones: Raiders of the Lost Ark\" (1981)**\n   - *Directed by Steven Spielberg*\n   - An adventurous romp following the archaeologist Indiana Jones in his quest for the Ark of the Covenant.\n\n9. **\"Mad Max: Fury Road\" (2015)**\n   - *Directed by George Miller*\n   - A high-octane action film set in a post-apocalyptic world, lauded for its stunning visuals and relentless pace.\n\n### **Science Fiction & Fantasy**\n\n10. **\"Blade Runner 2049\" (2017)**\n    - *Directed by Denis Villeneuve*\n    - A visually stunning sequel exploring themes of identity and humanity in a dystopian future.\n\n11. **\"The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring\" (2001)**\n    - *Directed by Peter Jackson*\n    - The beginning of an epic fantasy trilogy that brought J.R.R. Tolkien's world to life with groundbreaking effects and storytelling.\n\n12. **\"Inception\" (2010)**\n    - *Directed by Christopher Nolan*\n    - A mind-bending heist film set within the architecture of the mind, known for its complex narrative and visual spectacle.\n\n### **Comedy**\n\n13. **\"Some Like It Hot\" (1959)**\n    - *Directed by Billy Wilder*\n    - A classic screwball comedy featuring Marilyn Monroe, Tony Curtis, and Jack Lemmon in a hilarious tale of disguise and romance.\n\n14. **\"Monty Python and the Holy Grail\" (1975)**\n    - *Directed by Terry Gilliam and Terry Jones*\n    - A cult favorite comedy that parodies the Arthurian legend with absurd humor and memorable quotes.\n\n15. **\"Groundhog Day\" (1993)**\n    - *Directed by Harold Ramis*\n    - A clever comedy where the protagonist relives the same day repeatedly, blending humor with philosophical insights.\n\n### **Horror & Thriller**\n\n16. **\"The Shining\" (1980)**\n    - *Directed by Stanley Kubrick*\n    - A psychological horror film based on Stephen King's novel, renowned for its atmospheric tension and Jack Nicholson's performance.\n\n17. **\"Psycho\" (1960)**\n    - *Directed by Alfred Hitchcock*\n    - A seminal horror-thriller that redefined the genre with its suspenseful narrative and shocking twists.\n\n18. **\"Get Out\" (2017)**\n    - *Directed by Jordan Peele*\n    - A modern horror-thriller that combines social commentary with suspense, earning critical acclaim and a devoted following.\n\n### **Animated**\n\n19. **\"Spirited Away\" (2001)**\n    - *Directed by Hayao Miyazaki*\n    - A beautifully animated Japanese film that follows a young girl's journey through a mystical world, celebrated for its creativity and emotional depth.\n\n20. **\"Toy Story\" (1995)**\n    - *Directed by John Lasseter*\n    - The first feature-length film entirely animated with CGI, revolutionizing animation and telling a heartfelt story about toys coming to life.\n\n### **International**\n\n21. **\"Parasite\" (2019)**\n    - *Directed by Bong Joon-ho*\n    - A South Korean film that masterfully blends genres, exploring class disparity with sharp social commentary and gripping storytelling.\n\n22. **\"Seven Samurai\" (1954)**\n    - *Directed by Akira Kurosawa*\n    - A Japanese epic that follows a group of samurai defending a village from bandits, influential in cinema worldwide.\n\n23. **\"Am\u00e9lie\" (2001)**\n    - *Directed by Jean-Pierre Jeunet*\n    - A whimsical French film that portrays the life of a young woman in Paris as she decides to change the lives of those around her for the better.\n\n### **Documentary**\n\n24. **\"The Godfather\" (1972)**\n    - While not a documentary, it's often lauded similarly for its deep exploration of family and power structures within the Mafia.\n\n25. **\"13th\" (2016)**\n    - *Directed by Ava DuVernay*\n    - An insightful documentary that examines the intersection of race, justice, and mass incarceration in the United States.\n\n### **Modern Essentials**\n\n26. **\"La La Land\" (2016)**\n    - *Directed by Damien Chazelle*\n    - A modern musical that celebrates dreamers in Los Angeles, noted for its performances, music, and cinematography.\n\n27. **\"Black Panther\" (2018)**\n    - *Directed by Ryan Coogler*\n    - A culturally significant superhero film that combines action with themes of identity and responsibility.\n\n28. **\"Parasite\" (2019)**\n    - *Directed by Bong Joon-ho*\n    - A genre-blending masterpiece that delves into social inequality, becoming the first non-English film to win the Best Picture Oscar.\n\n### **Honorable Mentions**\n\n- **\"12 Angry Men\" (1957)**\n- **\"Pulp Fiction\" (1994)**\n- **\"The Matrix\" (1999)**\n- **\"One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest\" (1975)**\n- **\"Fight Club\" (1999)**\n\n### **Tips for Exploring the Best Movies**\n\n1. **Explore Different Genres:** Don't limit yourself to one genre. Exploring dramas, comedies, thrillers, and more can provide a well-rounded viewing experience.\n   \n2. **Watch International Films:** Films from different countries offer diverse perspectives and storytelling techniques.\n\n3. **Consider Critical and Audience Reviews:** Platforms like IMDb, Rotten Tomatoes, and Metacritic can help gauge a film's reception.\n\n4. **Look for Award-Winning Films:** Movies that have won or been nominated for major awards often showcase high-quality filmmaking.\n\n5. **Follow Recommendations:** Sometimes personal recommendations from friends or curated lists can lead you to hidden gems.\n\nRemember, the \"best\" movie for you is one that resonates with your personal tastes and interests. Enjoy your cinematic journey!",
